<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="113" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,469,998]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,865,890]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Uhler" authorityName="Uhler" box="[582,791,865,890]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sellatus">
<emphasis box="[582,702,865,890]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">H. sellatus</emphasis>
(Uhler)
</taxonomicName>
externally, but has a rather poorly defined median spot on the forewings. Although 
<bibRefCitation box="[429,827,901,926]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" refString="Subba Rao, V. R. &amp; Ramakrishnan, U. (1990) Two new species and a new record of Hishimonus ISH. from India. Reichenbachia, 28 (5), 27 - 31." type="journal article">
Subba Rao &amp; Ramakrishnan (
<number box="[761,819,902,926]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" value="1990.0">1990</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that the head is as wide as the pronotum, in the 
<typeStatus box="[192,290,937,962]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">holotype</typeStatus>
studied, the head is wider than the pronotum and the previous authority omitted showing a cross vein between the claval suture and the outer claval vein.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
